==Getting reverted== 
If you ever make a change that gets [[Wikipedia:Reverting|reverted]] by another editor, discuss the change on the  [[Wikipedia:Talk pages|talk page]]! The [[Wikipedia:BOLD, revert, discuss cycle|BOLD, revert, discuss cycle]] is a popular method of reaching consensus, and may be useful for identifying objections, keeping discussion moving forward and helping to break deadlocks.  [[Wikipedia:Edit warring|Edit warring]] (repeatedly overriding or reimplementing contributions) is highly discouraged.  There is a bright-line rule called the ''[[WP:3RR|three-revert rule]]'', the violation of which may lead someone to be [[WP:BLOCK|blocked]] from editing to prevent further disruption. [[WP:DISRUPTSIGNS|Disruptive editing]] is not always intentional, as new editors may simply not understand [[Wikipedia:Here to build an encyclopedia|the ins and outs of Wikipedia]]. 

